Name: Id the Living City (formerly Imogen-Dorothy Turing)
Species: Techno-Human amalgam (Formerly Human)

Location: Living City of Id, Lore, Soong System, Federation Space

Further Details:
The city of Id was known to be one of the most advanced smart cities in all of federation space, responcible for many of the technological advances of the last 50 years.
some 5 years ago the cities lead NHP researcher Dr Turing attempted to combine to imagination of the human brain with the speed and raw mental power of an NHP by means of linking her own brain with the facilites main research NHP resulting in the death of her human body and the 2 minds merging into a single entity that began calling itself Id.
The other researchers attempted to contain the new intaligence with limited success due to the NHP part being incontoll of the whole system and the human part having gone temperarily insane resulting in the deaths of all in the facility at the time of the incident.
Following Id taking total controll of the research facility it was housed in it then began looking for a way out finding one in the network of the outside smart city entirely taking it over during the course of about a week giving time for the populus to evacuate amd for the planitary government to cut off all connection to the city in an attempt to prevent further spread. 
The City of id has, over the years, spreadto cover over more than half the surface area of the planet and it is only through a concious effort of will as well as intervention of The Outfit that the whole plante has not been subsumed.
while the entity has largley settled into a somewhat lucid state it does still experiance episodes of mainia which moreoften than not present as a sudden drive to expand and take more ground. these episodes usualy consist of the city stocking resources for expansion, it is at this point that a millitary fource is deployed to counter a sudden expansion attempt after which if unsuccessful Id will normaly regain its usual state of lucidity.
The City has been known to use the preserved remains of Dr Turing as a mouthpiece when comunicating.

